    "description": "A smooth ergonomic handle/grip built with the Part workbench: four circular profile sketches stacked along Z with increasing then decreasing radius, blended into one solid by a smooth (non-ruled) loft, then softened with an all-edges fillet. This is the canonical pattern for organic curved shapes - controller grips, tool handles, ergonomic surfaces - where PartDesign's prismatic pad/pocket cannot produce the geometry. FreeCAD's own OCC kernel computes the real NURBS surface on recompute."
